##M 7th function notes

#What a function is
   #A function is a block of code that only runs when it is called. You can pass data, known as parameters, into a function. A function can return data as a result.
#why we use functions
   # it makes easier by redcuing code sizes
#How to write a function in Python
def greet():
    name=input("What is your name? ").strip().title()
    print("Hello, welcome to the program!")
#What parameters and arguments are
   #Parameters are the names used when defining a function or method, while arguments are the actual values you pass to the function when calling it.
#How to use parameters and arguments in python
def greet(name):  #name is the parameter
    print("Hello, " + name + ", welcome to the program!")
#What return statements are
   #used to exit a function and go back to the place where it was called.
#How to use return statements in a program
   #return value
